quran[24]{c,v,t}:
  37,103,"When they both submitted [to Allah’s command] and Abraham laid him on his forehead,"
  37,104,"and We called out to him, “O Abraham,"
  37,105,"You have fulfilled the dream.” This is how We reward those who do good."
  37,106,"This was indeed a revealing test."
  37,107,"And We ransomed him with a great sacrifice,"
  37,108,"and We left for him [a favorable mention] among later generations:"
  37,109,"“Peace be upon Abraham.”"
  37,110,"This is how We reward those who do good."
  37,111,"He was one of Our believing slaves."
  37,112,"And We gave him the glad tidings of Isaac, a prophet, and one of the righteous."
  37,113,"We blessed him and Isaac, but among their offspring were some who did good and some who clearly wronged themselves."
  37,114,"Indeed, We bestowed Our favor upon Moses and Aaron,"
  37,115,"and We saved them and their people from the great distress,"
  37,116,"and We helped them, so they were victorious,"
  37,117,"and We gave them both the clear Scripture,"
  37,118,"and guided them to the straight path;"
  37,119,"and We left for them [a favorable mention] among later generations:"
  37,120,"“Peace be upon Moses and Aaron.”"
  37,121,"This is how We reward those who do good."
  37,122,"They were truly of Our believing slaves."
  37,123,"Elijah was indeed one of the messengers."
  37,124,"When he said to his people: “Do you not fear Allah?"
  37,125,"Do you call upon Ba‘l and ignore the Best of the Creators,"
  37,126,"Allah, your Lord and the Lord of your forefathers?”"